    caption: [Diagrams showing how open and closed circulatory systems develop. The principal body cavity of arthropods is the hemocoel, which is formed by fusion of the primary blastocoel with the coelom.],
    path: "../fig/fig-2025-10-28-14-24-26.png"
  ),
